# Credibility Assessment Report: The FLCCC Alliance

## Introduction

The Front Line COVID-19 Critical Care Alliance (FLCCC Alliance) emerged during the COVID-19 pandemic as a group of physicians and healthcare professionals advocating for specific treatment protocols, notably involving the use of ivermectin and other therapies. Given the contentious nature of COVID-19 treatments and the proliferation of misinformation, assessing the credibility of the FLCCC Alliance is critical for healthcare professionals, policymakers, and the public.

This report provides a comprehensive, evidence-based analysis of the credibility of the FLCCC Alliance, drawing on detailed information about its members, activities, affiliations, and the scientific context surrounding its claims and protocols. The analysis prioritizes relevance, reliability, and significance of sources, with a focus on recent and authoritative information.

---

## Overview of the FLCCC Alliance

### Founding and Mission

The FLCCC Alliance is a group of physicians and clinical experts who developed treatment protocols for COVID-19, including the MATH+ and I-MASK+ protocols. Their stated mission is to improve patient outcomes through early treatment and critical care interventions.

